                   visual stimuli plays important role in V-BCI as it
                   decides the strength of visual signals in brain and
                   system communication rate. Recently new concept
                   called Hybrid V-BCI emerge based on concept of
                   combining advantages of one or more basic V-BCIs to
                   further enhance ITR and accuracy of system. In this
                   paper we review properties of brain signals involved
                   in V-BCI, stimulation methods used, hybrid V-BCI and
                   discuss current challenges in V-BCI with their
                   possible solutions.},
